Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place the @farro{3/4%cup} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat with 1 1/2 cups water, the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook about ~{30-35%minutes}, until farro is tender. Drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve any larger pieces of @butternut squash{12%oz}, then toss on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for about ~{20%minutes}, until golden brown and tender.

While squash and farro cook, halve the @leek{1} lengthwise. Then, thinly slice the pale green and white parts only, and rinse under cold water to remove any silt. @garlic{2%cloves} should be minced or grated. @mint{1%sprig} leaves should be chopped.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the leeks and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring, for about ~{6%minutes} or until tender. Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Set aside.

Once the squash is golden brown, add it to the pan with leeks and toss to combine. Stir in the mint and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Serve the squash and leek hash over the farro with a sprinkle of @pepitas{1%oz} and @feta cheese{1/4%cup} on top!

> Placing your baking sheet in the oven while it preheats will help ensure the butternut squash becomes fully caramelized and slightly crispy!